originalText.text: Small space with very helpful staff. Good machines are not overpriced.  Seating is provided.  Close to banks, restaurants, and stores . They're even close to MTA buses and subways.

originalText.text: Seems the workers prioritize the drop-off laundry because most machines are dedicated to that. There is a wait line for the other machines that are available. If you are washing a few items & not on a time limit, you can give them a try. I won’t be returning laundry time was doubled.

originalText.text: I’m never going to this laundromat again. I’ve had multiple clothes get ruined after doing laundry here. I had a shirt get shredded in the washer and most recently had a pair of jeans ruined with multiple holes and small tears. The staff is really rude as well. I would avoid it at all costs.

originalText.text: I give this place 3 stars only because it’s how I honestly view this laundromat as a whole as far as space, staff, cleanliness, professionalism and ease of access to the machines. There are more than enough washers however I feel that for me, the issue is there aren’t enough dryers and one tends to get stuck waiting for dryers and also waiting for the staff to finish drying clothes for the clients who drop off their laundry. NOW*As far as their drop off service is concerned, they do a phenomenal job. Never have had any issues Or problems and I don’t think the price is too much. It’s about 12 dollars for a small load to be washed and folded by the staffs drop off service* if you happen to forget your ticket just let the staff know and ask if they can look it up by name and they will gladly do it.

originalText.text: Place is affordable, but very small, gets crowded easily. I advise you do laundry Monday thru Wednesday if you can because it's less crowded. I also advise that you go early before 4pm because the owner starts closing procedures early and get upset when you want to do your laundry after 4pm. Otherwise it's convenient, if you don't mind people and rude old ladies *hint, hint, the owner, hint hint* then be my guest!
